    <h2><strong>2. E-liquid Capacity (ML):</strong></h2>

    <p>Both <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> and the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> have generous e-liquid capacities. <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> features <strong>13 mL</strong>, while the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> offers <strong>10 mL</strong>, ensuring users have ample e-liquid for their vaping sessions.</p>

    <h2><strong>3. Battery Capacity (mAh):</strong></h2>

    <p>The <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> features a larger <strong>1500 mAh</strong> battery capacity, whereas <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> offers a respectable <strong>600 mAh</strong> capacity. Despite the lower capacity, <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> provides sufficient power for a satisfying vaping experience.</p>

    <h2><strong>4. Price and Cost Efficiency:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> is attractively priced at <strong>$27.99</strong>, with a cost per milliliter of e-liquid at <strong>$2.15</strong>. In comparison, the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> is priced at <strong>$25.99</strong>, with a slightly higher cost per milliliter at <strong>$2.60</strong>. This cost efficiency makes <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> a cost-effective choice for budget-conscious vapers.</p>
     
      <h2><strong>5. Release Date:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> was released in <strong>Q1 2023</strong>, whereas the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> hit the market in <strong>Q3 2022</strong>. There's a slight time difference in their release dates.</p>

    <h2><strong>6. Flavor Variety:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> offers an impressive selection of <strong>22</strong> flavors, providing users with a wide array of options. In contrast, the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> offers <strong>15</strong> flavors.</p>

    <h2><strong>7. Rechargeable:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> is rechargeable, offering users a more eco-friendly and cost-effective vaping solution. In contrast, the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> is not rechargeable.</p>

    <h2><strong>8. Special Features:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> stands out with its features, including a mesh coil for enhanced flavor, sweet flavor options, rechargeability, and a convenient USB Type-C port. Additionally, it is noted for its ergonomic shape, providing users with a comfortable grip. <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong>, while featuring a mesh coil, lacks rechargeability and some of the advanced features offered by <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong>.</p>

    <h2><strong>9. Flavor Profile:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> is described as "<strong>very sweet</strong>," making it an ideal choice for vapers seeking sweet and flavorful vaping experiences. On the other hand, the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> is described as "<strong>less sweet</strong>."</p>

    <p>In conclusion, based on the provided data and key factors, <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> emerges as the superior choice. It offers a significantly higher puff count, competitive pricing, rechargeability, a wide range of flavors, and advanced features such as USB Type-C connectivity and an ergonomic shape for user comfort. While the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> offers a larger battery capacity, it falls behind in puff count, cost efficiency, and features. <strong>VICE BOX 6000</strong> is the top pick for vapers seeking a budget-friendly, sweet, and versatile vaping experience.</p>
